Prudential Investors May Vote Against Chairman, Mail Says

-- B y   S i m o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-05-08T13:07:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/prudential-investors-may-vote-against-chairman-mail-says.html
Some investors in  Prudential Plc (PRU) , the
U.K.’s biggest insurer, may vote against the re-election of
Chairman Harvey McGrath, the  Mail on Sunday  reported, citing
shareholders it didn’t identify.  Prudential’s directors have put themselves up for re-
election at the annual meeting on May 19 after last year’s
unsuccessful bid for AIA Group Ltd., the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Clark in London at 
 sclark4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at   eevans3@bloomberg.net  